# Backport of vllm-project/vllm#45426: sparse MLA DCP + fp8 KV-cache for
# DeepSeek-V3.2 / GLM-5.2.
#
# Adds --dcp-sparse-indexer-mode (union/exact) for sparse MLA attention under
# Decode Context Parallelism, plus fp8 KV-cache support (LSE return, head
# envelope checks, -1 top-k masking) for the FlashMLA sparse backend.
#
# v0.25.0 upstream (#46076) absorbed the shared indexer DCP plumbing and added
# its own always-on exact merge that emits GLOBAL token ids for the FlashInfer
# sparse backend (SM100-only). This patch replaces that merge with the
# mode-gated local-index merge the FlashMLA sparse path consumes: "union"
# (production) skips the merge entirely; "exact" runs the deterministic
# candidate all-gather. FlashInfer sparse + DCP is rejected at startup since
# its global-id contract no longer holds under this patch.
#
# Upstream PR: https://github.com/vllm-project/vllm/pull/45426 (closed,
# superseded by https://github.com/vllm-project/vllm/pull/46514, still open —
# note #46514 dropped the union mode in its 2026-07-12 rebase; retiring this
# patch when it lands means production switches to exact-merge semantics).
# Tested against: vllm v0.25.0 (vllm/vllm-openai:v0.25.0-ubuntu2404)
